## Get started with Chef server

If you don't have a Chef server, the [Manage a node](/modules/manage-a-node/rhel/) tutorial gets you started. You'll learn how Chef server acts as a central repository for your cookbooks as well as for information about every node it manages.

You'll bring up a Chef server, either through our hosted service or in your own environment, and learn how to manage a Red Hat Enterprise Linux or CentOS server remotely from your workstation.

In the later part of this tutorial, you'll bootstrap your CentOS node to the Chef server. This enables your node to pull down the remediation cookbook you'll build in the next part.

