## Learn about local development using Test Kitchen

If you're not familiar with local development using Test Kitchen, check out the [Get started with Test Kitchen](/modules/local-development/rhel/) tutorial.

You'll learn how to use Test Kitchen along with the virtualization tools VirtualBox and Vagrant to develop and verify your infrastructure code _before_ you apply the configuration to your production servers.

<%= link_to("Start the Get started with Test Kitchen tutorial <i class='fa fa-angle-double-right'></i>", "/local-development/rhel/", class: 'button radius cta cta') %>

As an optional exercise, the [Develop a web app cookbook](/manage-a-web-app/rhel/) tutorial provides additional hands-on practice with local development. Here, you configure a basic but complete web application using Test Kitchen.

The _Develop a web app cookbook_ tutorial introduces many new Chef concepts, and can take some time to complete. To save time, you can perform the [quickstart](/manage-a-web-app/rhel/bring-up-the-web-app-using-test-kitchen/) to bring up the final configuration on a local test instance in just a few minutes and then read through the tutorial to see how it's built.

